description: Title: MongoDB Migration System with Mongoose (TypeScript)  Description: This is a lightweight migration system for MongoDB using Mongoose in TypeScript. It allows you to manage database schema or data changes safely by running migrations once and only once.  Features:  Tracks executed migrations in a migrations collection.  Supports multiple migrations with versioning and descriptions.  Logs progress and errors during execution.  Example migration included: drops problematic barcode indexes from the products collection.  Usage:  Add migrations to the migrations array.  Call runMigrations() to apply any pending migrations.  Each migration is executed only if it hasn't run before.  This system is perfect for projects where database schema or data needs controlled updates across environments.
